// place-tavern.ipt
// =====================================================================
// A tavern / alehouse — a drinking and social hub, distinct from the
// inn. Where the inn is about lodging and a night's stay, the tavern
// is about the drink, the regulars, the games, and what the place is
// the heart of. No rooms; this is where the neighbourhood gathers,
// gossips, gambles, and occasionally brawls.
//
// Entry table: [@TF-Tavern]
//
// Inputs (optional, via API promptValues):
//   prompt1 town  /  prompt2 shopType (display)  /  prompt3 shopName
//
// Reuses people.ipt + prices.ipt. Drink prices in COPPER
// (1 gp = 100 cp); mostly approximations (~), verify to taste.

Title: Tavern
Use: people.ipt
Use: prices.ipt

Prompt: town {} an unnamed town
Prompt: shopType {} tavern
Prompt: shopName {} 

Table: TF-Tavern
Set: town={$prompt1}
Set: passedName={$prompt3}
Set: m=[@Markup]
Set: keep=[@PersonName]
Set: kanc=[@Ancestry]
**[@TavernTitle]** *(tavern in {$town})*\n&
**[@TavernKind], [@TavernCrowd]**\n&
**Behind the bar:** {$keep}, a [@PersonDesc] {$kanc} who is [@Personality].\n&
**House specialty:** [@HouseSpecialty]\n&
**On tap & on offer** ({$markupReason}):\n&
[@DrinkList]\n&
**The entertainment:** [@TavernEntertainment]\n&
**The regulars:** [@TavernRegular]\n&
**{$keep} says:** "[@TavernQuote]"\n&
**Trouble at the bar:** [@TavernHook]

Table: TavernTitle
[when]{$passedName}=[do][@TavernName][else]{$passedName}[end]

Table: TavernName
The [@TavernNameAdj] [@TavernNameNoun]
The [@TavernNameNoun] and [@TavernNameNoun]

Table: TavernNameAdj
Thirsty
Drunken
Rowdy
Singing
Bottomless
Old
Merry
Sly
Three-Legged
Roaring

Table: TavernNameNoun
Cask
Flagon
Crow
Fiddle
Boar
Wench
Cellar
Stoat
Whistle
Barrel
Cup
Dog

Table: TavernKind
A cramped, smoky alehouse where everyone knows everyone
A big, raucous drinking-hall that fills every night
A dockside dive where the drink is cheap and the company rough
A respectable public house favoured by tradesfolk
A cellar bar reached by a flight of worn steps
A faded old tavern coasting on its better days
A tavern that doubles as the neighbourhood's unofficial moot-hall

Table: TavernCrowd
packed and loud tonight
half-full, with the serious drinkers settled in
quiet, just a few regulars nursing their cups
rowdy, one song away from a sing-along or a scuffle
tense, with two groups keeping a careful distance
oddly subdued, as if waiting for something

Table: HouseSpecialty
a dark, near-black stout the regulars swear by
a fierce spiced spirit that the keeper distils out back
honeyed mead by the jug, sweet enough to be dangerous
a sour country cider that grows on you
a foreign wine no one can pronounce and everyone orders
"the usual" — a murky house ale of mysterious composition
a hot mulled drink that's the only reason to brave winter here

Table: DrinkList
- Mug of house ale ........... (~) [@PricedAs with 2]\n&
- The house specialty ........ (~) [@PricedAs with 5]\n&
- Cup of wine ................ (~) [@PricedAs with 4]\n&
- A strong measure of spirits  (~) [@PricedAs with 8]\n&
- Bread, cheese, and pickles . (~) [@PricedAs with 3]\n&
- A whole jug, to share ...... (~) [@PricedAs with 12]

Table: TavernEntertainment
a fiddler and a drummer working the crowd toward dancing
a storyteller holding a rapt table with tall tales
dice and cards at every other table, coin changing hands fast
a darts contest that's getting more competitive than friendly
a singer whose sad songs have half the room misty-eyed
arm-wrestling matches with side bets piling up
nothing organised — just the roar of a hundred conversations
a travelling performer trying out new material, with mixed results

Table: TavernRegular
{!reg==[@PersonName]}{!ranc==[@Ancestry]}{$reg}, a [@PersonDesc] {$ranc}, [@RegularDoing]

Table: RegularDoing
holds the same stool every night and knows everyone's business
is three drinks past wise and looking for an argument
quietly buys a round whenever the talk turns to a certain subject
nurses one drink for hours and watches the door
is winning at cards and making no friends doing it
will tell their war stories to anyone who'll sit still
came in looking for someone and is running out of patience
is the keeper's eyes and ears, paid in free ale

Table: TavernQuote
First one's poured, the rest you earn. What'll it be?
No fighting in my house. Take it to the alley like civilised folk.
You drink, you pay, you behave. Two of three and we'll get along.
Everyone's welcome 'til they're not. Don't be the one who's not.
The specialty'll put hair on your chest and holes in your memory.
Coin on the bar or stories in my ear — I'll take either.
I've heard every excuse for a free drink. Surprise me.

Table: TavernHook
a brawl is brewing over something that happened a week ago
someone's been buying drinks for strangers and asking pointed questions
a regular hasn't shown in days and the keeper is worried
a fight last night ended badly and the watch hasn't been told
the keeper is being leaned on to host meetings they want no part of
a stranger drank themselves senseless muttering about a treasure
two patrons are quietly arranging something illegal in the corner
a tab has run impossibly high and the debtor has stopped coming in
someone slipped something into a drink, and it wasn't meant for who got it

// Standalone name roll (collision-proof, for note titles etc.).
Table: TF-TavernName
[@TavernName]
